# Home Wi-Fi SSIDs for the auto-reconnect feature (plugins/wifi.sh).
#
# Copy this file to "wifi_home_ssids" (same folder) and list one SSID per line.
# When you are connected to one of these networks AND the signal drops to 1 bar,
# wifi.sh bounces Wi-Fi off/on so macOS reconnects to the strongest access point.
#
# - One SSID per line, exact name (case-sensitive).
# - Lines starting with # and blank lines are ignored.
# - Any number of SSIDs works (even 1). If "wifi_home_ssids" is missing or has no
#   SSIDs, auto-reconnect is OFF (the strength icon still works regardless).
#
# Example:
# MyHome-Living
# MyHome-Bedroom
